body:
## Summary

A `SELECT` from a view built out of several `UNION ALL` / `UNION DISTINCT` branches throws

```
Code: 49. DB::Exception: Block structure mismatch in UnionStep stream: different columns:
old_value String String(size = 0)
old_value String Const(size = 0, String(size = 1)). (LOGICAL_ERROR)
```

One branch's projection for the `old_value` column self-deduplicates into a `Const` column while the sibling branch keeps a full `String` column, so `UnionStep` rejects the divergent headers. This happens with default settings (`query_plan_merge_filters=1`, analyzer on) and aborts the server on debug/sanitizer builds.

## How to reproduce

Deterministic on current `master` (`26.7.1.1292`) with default settings, both in `clickhouse local` and against a running server:

```sql
DROP VIEW IF EXISTS default.repro_vw;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.repro_eo;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.repro_eo_ksa;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.repro_te;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.repro_etc;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.repro_etc_ksa;

CREATE TABLE default.repro_eo (event_id String, order_number Nullable(UInt32), created_at DateTime, ticket_id Nullable(String), event_name String, field_name Nullable(String), old_value Nullable(String), new_value Nullable(String), author_id Nullable(String)) ENGINE=MergeTree ORDER BY (created_at, event_id);
CREATE TABLE default.repro_eo_ksa AS default.repro_eo;
CREATE TABLE default.repro_te (event_id String, order_number UInt8, created_at DateTime, ticket_id String, event_name Nullable(String), field_name Nullable(String), old_value Nullable(String), new_value Nullable(String), author_id Nullable(String), recipients Nullable(String), interactive_elements Nullable(String), owner_type Nullable(String)) ENGINE=MergeTree ORDER BY (created_at, event_id);
CREATE TABLE default.repro_etc (event_id String, order_number UInt8, created_at DateTime, ticket_id String, event_name String, field_name String, old_value String, new_value String, author_id Nullable(String), recipients Nullable(String), interactive_elements Nullable(String), owner_type String) ENGINE=MergeTree ORDER BY (created_at, event_id);
CREATE TABLE default.repro_etc_ksa AS default.repro_etc;

INSERT INTO default.repro_eo     SELECT toString(number),0, now()-toIntervalDay(1), toString(number%100),'ticket.updated','queue_id','ov','nv',NULL FROM numbers(5000);
INSERT INTO default.repro_eo_ksa SELECT toString(number),0, now()-toIntervalDay(1), toString(number%100),'ticket.updated','queue_id','ov','nv',NULL FROM numbers(5000);
INSERT INTO default.repro_te     SELECT toString(number),0, now()-toIntervalDay(1), toString(number%100), if(number%2=0,'basket.ticket.added','other'),'f','ov','nv','auth','rec','ie','ot' FROM numbers(5000);
INSERT INTO default.repro_etc     SELECT toString(number),0, now()-toIntervalDay(1), toString(number%100),'grp.changed','group','ov','nv','auth','rec','ie','ot' FROM numbers(5000);
INSERT INTO default.repro_etc_ksa SELECT toString(number),0, now()-toIntervalDay(1), toString(number%100),'grp.changed','group','ov','nv','auth','rec','ie','ot' FROM numbers(5000);

CREATE VIEW default.repro_vw AS
WITH crm AS (
  SELECT event_id, toUInt8(coalesce(order_number,0)) AS order_number, created_at, assumeNotNull(coalesce(ticket_id,'')) AS ticket_id, assumeNotNull(multiIf(event_name='basket.added','basket.ticket.added', event_name='basket.removed','basket.ticket.removed', event_name='ticket.updated','ticket.updated','')) AS event_name, assumeNotNull(coalesce(field_name,'')) AS field_name, assumeNotNull(coalesce(old_value,'')) AS old_value, assumeNotNull(coalesce(new_value,'')) AS new_value, author_id, '' AS recipients, '' AS interactive_elements, '' AS owner_type, 'crm' AS source, 'non-ksa' AS country_of_ticket FROM default.repro_eo WHERE (event_name IN ('basket.added','basket.removed')) OR ((event_name='ticket.updated') AND (field_name='queue_id'))
  UNION ALL
  SELECT event_id, toUInt8(coalesce(order_number,0)) AS order_number, created_at, assumeNotNull(coalesce(ticket_id,'')) AS ticket_id, assumeNotNull(multiIf(event_name='basket.added','basket.ticket.added', event_name='basket.removed','basket.ticket.removed', event_name='ticket.updated','ticket.updated','')) AS event_name, assumeNotNull(coalesce(field_name,'')) AS field_name, assumeNotNull(coalesce(old_value,'')) AS old_value, assumeNotNull(coalesce(new_value,'')) AS new_value, author_id, '' AS recipients, '' AS interactive_elements, '' AS owner_type, 'crm' AS source, 'ksa' AS country_of_ticket FROM default.repro_eo_ksa WHERE (event_name IN ('basket.added','basket.removed')) OR ((event_name='ticket.updated') AND (field_name='queue_id'))
),
hd_3001_0202 AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT event_id, toUInt8(coalesce(order_number,0)) AS order_number, created_at, ticket_id, assumeNotNull(coalesce(event_name,'')) AS event_name, 'agent_id' AS field_name, assumeNotNull(if(event_name='basket.ticket.added','', coalesce(author_id,''))) AS old_value, assumeNotNull(if(event_name='basket.ticket.added', coalesce(author_id,''),'')) AS new_value, NULL AS author_id, recipients, interactive_elements, coalesce(owner_type,'') AS owner_type FROM default.repro_te WHERE repro_te.event_name IN ('basket.ticket.removed','basket.ticket.added')
  UNION ALL
  SELECT event_id, toUInt8(coalesce(order_number,0)) AS order_number, created_at, ticket_id, assumeNotNull(coalesce(event_name,'')) AS event_name, assumeNotNull(coalesce(field_name,'')) AS field_name, assumeNotNull(coalesce(old_value,'')) AS old_value, assumeNotNull(coalesce(new_value,'')) AS new_value, author_id, recipients, interactive_elements, assumeNotNull(coalesce(owner_type,'')) AS owner_type FROM default.repro_te WHERE repro_te.event_name NOT IN ('basket.ticket.removed','basket.ticket.added')
),
hd AS (
  SELECT *, 'hd' AS source, 'non-ksa' AS country_of_ticket FROM default.repro_etc WHERE (created_at < '2026-01-30 10:14:27') OR (created_at > '2026-02-02 15:00:00')
  UNION DISTINCT
  SELECT *, 'hd' AS source, 'non-ksa' AS country_of_ticket FROM hd_3001_0202
  UNION DISTINCT
  SELECT *, 'hd' AS source, 'ksa' AS country_of_ticket FROM default.repro_etc_ksa
),
result AS (SELECT * FROM crm UNION ALL SELECT * FROM hd)
SELECT * FROM result;

SELECT count() FROM default.repro_vw WHERE created_at >= now() - toIntervalDay(7);
```

The final `SELECT count()` throws the `LOGICAL_ERROR` above.

## Bisect

`git bisect` over `master` first-parent CI builds (release, default settings) points at the sync merge of this PR:

Caused by: https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse/pull/106113

Verified directly:

- **Good** — `87e40606` (`26.6.1.1250`), the parent right before the merge: the query returns `25000`.
- **Bad** — the `106113` merge (`26.6.1.1251`) and every build since, up to current `master` `26.7.1.1292`: `LOGICAL_ERROR`.

The self-deduplication introduced by that PR collapses the `old_value` projection subtree in one union branch into a canonical `Const` node, while the sibling branch keeps a full column; the strict `UnionStep` header check then rejects the `Const`-vs-full divergence.

## Related

- Related: https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse/issues/106956 — an adjacent `Block structure mismatch in UnionStep stream` where a branch's `WHERE` predicate constant-folds after filter push-down **through a join** (fixed by https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse/pull/107041 via `materializeConstantsForSetOperationBranches`). That case reproduces independently of the self-dedup optimization and is a **different** path; the fix does not cover the dedup-driven `Const` divergence reported here.

## Environment

- Reproduced on `master` `26.7.1.1292` and first affected build `26.6.1.1251`; not present on `26.6.1.1250`.
- Release build, default settings, `x86_64`.
